INSERT INTO `pages` VALUES (1,3,'<p>\n	<strong>Operating System</strong></p>\n<p>\n	10Layer operates on Linux. It could potentially also run on other Unix and OSX-based systems. Debian or Ubuntu are recommended.</p>\n<p>\n	<strong>Databases</strong></p>\n<p>\n	MySql and MongoDB are required.</p>\n<p>\n	<strong>Servers</strong></p>\n<p>\n	10Layer can operate on a variety of Web servers, provided they support PHP. Apache is recommended.</p>\n<p>\n	The Orbited comet server is required.</p>\n<p>\n	A Solr server running on Tomcat will be required in future releases of 10Layer, but is not currently required.</p>\n<p>\n	<strong>PHP</strong></p>\n<p>\n	PHP 5.2 or greater is recommended. PHP 5.3 has also been tested successfully.&nbsp;</p>\n<p>\n	The PHP ImageMagick (php-imagick) module is required.</p>\n'),(2,73,'<p>\n	<b>10Layer</b><br />\n	<a href=\"mailto:info@10layer.com\">info@10layer.com</a><br />\n	<a href=\"http://www.twitter.com/10layer\">Twitter</a></p>\n<p>\n	<strong>Jason Norwood-Young</strong><br />\n	CTO and CEO<br />\n	<a href=\"mailto:jason@10layer.com\">jason@10layer.com</a><br />\n	<a href=\"http://www.twitter.com/j_norwood_young\">Twitter</a> | <a href=\"http://www.facebook.com/jnorwoodyoung\">Facebook</a></p>\n<p>\n	<strong>Guy Taylor</strong><br />\n	MD<br />\n	<a href=\"mailto:guy@10layer.com\">guy@10layer.com</a><br />\n	<a href=\"http://www.twitter.com/xsyn\">Twitter</a> | <a href=\"http://www.facebook.com/guy.taylor\">Facebook</a></p>\n'),(3,74,'<p>\n	10Layer creates publishing frameworks for big online news publishers.</p>\n'),(4,88,'<p>\n	This is a test</p>\n'),(5,329,'<p>\n	&nbsp;</p>\n<p class=\"p1\">\n	<strong>Jason Norwood-Young, CEO</strong></p>\n<p class=\"p1\">\n	<img alt=\"Jason Norwood-Young\" src=\"http://c714723.r23.cf2.rackcdn.com/jason.png\" style=\"margin-left: 10px; margin-right: 10px; margin-top: 10px; margin-bottom: 10px; float: right; width: 200px; height: 300px; \" />Jason&#39;s career blends IT and journalism over the past 15 years. He&#39;s been a journalist, technology editor, deputy editor, associate editor and editor on multiple publications, including ITWeb, ITWeb Brainstorm, and Stuff Magazine.&nbsp;</p>\n<p class=\"p1\">\n	He previously headed the technical division of Mail &amp; Guardian Online, Africa&#39;s oldest news website.&nbsp;</p>\n<p class=\"p1\">\n	<strong>email</strong> <a href=\"mailto:jason@10layer.com\">jason@10layer.com</a><br />\n	<strong>twitter</strong>&nbsp;<a href=\"http://twitter.com/j_norwood_young\">j_norwood_young</a><br />\n	<strong>im</strong> jason@freespeechpub.co.za<br />\n	<strong>facebook</strong> <a href=\"http://www.facebook.com/jnorwoodyoung\">jnorwoodyoung</a><br />\n	<strong>google</strong>&nbsp;<a href=\"https://plus.google.com/u/0/103914093171434290955\">j.norwood.young@gmail.com</a><br />\n	<b>skype</b> j_norwood_young<br />\n	<strong>phone</strong> +27-84-680-3445</p>\n<p class=\"p1\">\n	&nbsp;</p>\n<p class=\"p1\">\n	&nbsp;</p>\n<p class=\"p1\">\n	&nbsp;</p>\n<p class=\"p1\">\n	&nbsp;</p>\n<p class=\"p1\">\n	&nbsp;</p>\n<p class=\"p1\">\n	&nbsp;</p>\n<p class=\"p1\">\n	<strong>Guy Taylor, MD</strong></p>\n<p class=\"p1\">\n	<img alt=\"Guy Taylor\" src=\"http://c714723.r23.cf2.rackcdn.com/guy.png\" style=\"margin-left: 10px; margin-right: 10px; margin-top: 10px; margin-bottom: 10px; float: right; width: 200px; height: 300px; \" />Guy was recently showcased in the Mail &amp; Guardian&rsquo;s 200 Young South Africans to Take to Lunch. It describes him as follows:</p>\n<p class=\"p1\">\n	Guy Taylor is addicted to change -- changing systems, behaviours, frameworks; anything that helps business move into a more human space. As a behavioural theorist, analyst and change agent, Taylor works with social tools that will create freedom of thought, interaction and community and provides the technology to make it happen. Why? Because he believes that business is done in a way that doesn&rsquo;t makes sense to people.&nbsp;</p>\n<p class=\"p1\">\n	<strong>email</strong>&nbsp;<a href=\"mailto:guy@10layer.com\">guy@10layer.com</a><br />\n	<strong>twitter</strong>&nbsp;<a href=\"http://twitter.com/xsyn\">xsyn</a><br />\n	<strong>im, google</strong>&nbsp;guy.taylor@gmail.com<br />\n	<strong>facebook</strong>&nbsp;<a href=\"http://www.facebook.com/guy.taylor\">guy.taylor</a><br />\n	<strong>phone</strong>&nbsp;+27-83-357-3438</p>\n<p class=\"p1\">\n	&nbsp;</p>\n<p class=\"p1\">\n	&nbsp;</p>\n<p class=\"p1\">\n	&nbsp;</p>\n<p class=\"p1\">\n	&nbsp;</p>\n<p class=\"p1\">\n	&nbsp;</p>\n<p class=\"p1\">\n	<strong>10Layer</strong></p>\n<p class=\"p1\">\n	To get hold of the 10Layer team, you can mail <a href=\"mailto:team@10layer.com\">team@10layer.com</a>. Hit us up on Twitter at <a href=\"http://twitter.com/10layer\">@10Layer</a>.</p>\n<p class=\"p1\">\n	&nbsp;</p>\n<p class=\"p1\">\n	See Jason and Guy talking about 10Layer on <a href=\"http://dogreatthings.co.za/guide/entrepreneurs/jason_norwood-young\">Old Mutual&#39;s Entrepreneur&#39;s Guide</a>, or watch the video below.</p>\n<p class=\"p1\">\n	&nbsp;</p>\n<p>\n	<iframe allowfullscreen=\"\" frameborder=\"0\" height=\"315\" src=\"http://www.youtube.com/embed/M6GNrWv37Rc?rel=0\" width=\"560\"></iframe></p>\n'),(6,330,'<p>\n	<strong>Mail &amp; Guardian Online</strong></p>\n<p>\n	The&nbsp;<i>Mail &amp; Guardian Online</i>&nbsp;was the first internet-based news publications in Africa. Launched in early 1994, it is one of South Africa&#39;s and Africa&#39;s major news publishers and is reputed internationally for its quality content. Today, it is a fast-growing site, taking its place as one of country&#39;s top three biggest news sites.&nbsp;</p>\n<p>\n	<a href=\"http://mg.co.za\">Visit mg.co.za</a></p>\n<p>\n	<strong>Daily Maverick</strong></p>\n<p>\n	The Daily Maverick is a unique blend of news, information, analysis and opinion delivered from our newsroom in Johannesburg, South Africa. There are many ways to describe exactly what we do (and for the price of a cup of coffee we&#39;ll talk your ears off about it), but the best way to understand the end result is to experience it. Every part of The Daily Maverick is free-to-air and no-payment-required, although free registration is required for a small subset of functions and pages.</p>\n<p>\n	<a href=\"http://dailymaverick.co.za\">Visit dailymaverick.co.za</a></p>\n<p>\n	<strong>iMaverick</strong></p>\n<p>\n	South Africa&#39;s first iPad daily newspaper, from the team that brought you Daily Maverick.&nbsp;</p>\n<p class=\"p1\">\n	Written by the same people who won the Bookmark Best Editorial Team in South Africa 2010 award, everything else will seem staid and outdated by comparison.</p>\n<p class=\"p1\">\n	<a href=\"http://imaverick.co.za\">Visit imaverick.co.za</a></p>\n'),(7,331,'<p>\n	<strong>PHP Jedi&nbsp;</strong></p>\n<p class=\"p1\">\n	<em>Cape Town or Johannesburg&nbsp;</em></p>\n<p class=\"p1\">\n	Yo, devs! 10Layer is looking for a PHP Jedi.</p>\n<p class=\"p1\">\n	10Layer is a South African startup focussed on building the tools that news publishers use to publish online. We believe in open source, a free media, and delivering software that real people can -- and want to -- use.</p>\n<p class=\"p1\">\n	We&rsquo;re looking for a top-notch developer looking to work on really exciting projects. You&rsquo;ll be helping to create 10Layer itself, as well as working on some of the best content sites in South Africa. You&rsquo;ll be expected to be creative, self-motivated, experimental and imaginative. You shouldn&rsquo;t be satisfied in doing something the same way as its always been done. You should have a burning desire to make things work better.</p>\n<p class=\"p1\">\n	You&rsquo;ll need to be a PHP expert, and your Javascript must be strong too. You&rsquo;ll need to know about both front and back-end website design and development. You need to be able to architect full solutions, from the server, through the software stack, to a final product. You&rsquo;ll need to know about managing everything once it&rsquo;s rolled out too.</p>\n<p class=\"p1\">\n	Bonus points if you&rsquo;re into Python, Objective C, and Ruby.&nbsp;</p>\n<p class=\"p1\">\n	And mostly we&rsquo;re looking for someone willing and hungry to learn.</p>\n<p class=\"p1\">\n	Apply at <a href=\"mailto:jobs@10layer.com?subject=PHP%20Jedi%20position\">jobs@10layer.com</a>.</p>\n'),(8,342,'<p>\n	We&#39;ll be setting up a demo site soon. In the meantime, if you&#39;d like to see the product, please <a href=\"mailto:info@10layer.com?subject=Demo%20request\">contact us</a> and we&#39;ll show you the product personally.</p>\n'),(9,343,'<p>\n	<textarea readonly=\"readonly\" style=\"height: 800px; width: 600px\">COPYRIGHT 10LAYER SOFTWARE DEVELOPMENT PTY (LTD)\n\n10LAYER LICENCE\n\nVersion 1.1 / August 2011\n\nTHE SYSTEM IS PROVIDED TO YOU, AN INDIVIDUAL OR LEGAL ENTITY, UNDER THE TERMS OF THIS LICENCE (&quot;LICENCE&quot;) ISSUED BY THE LICENSOR, 10LAYER SOFTWARE DEVELOPMENT (PTY) LTD BEING A PRIVATE COMPANY, WHOSE PRINCIPAL PLACE OF BUSINESS IS 77 12TH STREET, ORANGE GROVE, JOHANNESBURG, SOUTH AFRICA. THE SYSTEM IS PROTECTED BY COPYRIGHT AND/OR OTHER APPLICABLE LAW. ANY USE OF THE SYSTEM OTHER THAN AS AUTHORIZED UNDER THIS LICENCE OR COPYRIGHT LAW IS PROHIBITED. BY EXERCISING ANY RIGHTS TO THE SYSTEM PROVIDED HERE, YOU ACCEPT AND AGREE TO BE BOUND BY THE TERMS OF THIS LICENCE. TO THE EXTENT THIS LICENCE MAY BE CONSIDERED TO BE A CONTRACT, THE LICENSOR GRANTS YOU THE RIGHTS CONTAINED HERE IN CONSIDERATION OF YOUR ACCEPTANCE OF SUCH TERMS AND CONDITIONS.\n\n	1.	DEFINITIONS\n	1.1	&quot;Adaptation&quot; means software or other systems based upon the 10Layer System;\n	1.2	&quot;Agreement&quot; shall mean this Agreement and the supporting documentation incorporated by reference.\n	1.3	&quot;Distribute&quot; means to make available to the public the original and copies of the System, as appropriate, through sale, license or transfer of ownership.\n	1.4	&quot;Licence Models&quot; means the va